cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CR

The paper presents a novel target encoding scheme for improving the performance of neural network models in image classification tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the robustness of the proposed method against adversarial attacks, which suggests the possibility of it belonging to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper involves optimization techniques, which could place it in the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category.
